{
  "stem": "9590.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] For us, for my mother, for my brother, and for me, it was like the end of the world for us.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My father was 40 years old, was healthy.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "I don't remember a day that my father was sick or complaining about anything.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And then one day, he was gone.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] We were in danger, too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "Living under the German occupation, every day brought something else.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "Very sad news.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "Here, the authorities wanted from the Jews all the gold they possessed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "Then they asked for furs.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "Then they asked for silver, for precious metals.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "For whatever one had, they asked.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And everybody had to give it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "Otherwise, life was at stake.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] After a while, a Judenrat was formed in our shtetl.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "A Judenrat means that there was like an administration.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "There was somebody responsible, that the authorities spoke to them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "They couldn't speak to every Jew separate.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "They gave an order to the Judenrat, and the Judenrat told the rest of the people, you must bring your possessions.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "Otherwise our life is at stake.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "And that's what most people did.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "We tried to hide some of the possessions that we had, not to be left without anything.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "But basically, it was handed to them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Then they formed a closed ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "Half of the city was moved into the other part of the city.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "The house that we lived remained in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "And another family came to live with us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] We took it in our stride, because we had no alternative.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "My mother tried very hard to provide for us the necessities.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "And that's how life was from day to day.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
